Bookman Old Style Bold Italic (Bookosbi.ttf)

OS/2, usWeightClass

MS NID 2

usWeightClass should be 700 if MS ID 2 is 'Bold'.

ID 2 is 'Bold Italic'
usWeightClass is '600'
but should be 700. Otherwiese it may cause style linking issues in MS Office and/or fonts are hidden in font folder on Windows (if NID 1 is eqaul to another font and usWeightClass is the same.).

Bookman Old Style Regular (Bookos.ttf)

name

MS NID 7/13

License text, if Trademark (NID 7) is 'The Monotype Corporation'

License text contains 'Monotype Imaging Inc'.
Normally you should just keep it as it was in the original data (often that entry is non-existing). Just double check. It shouldn't be related to Monotype Imaging Inc! In case of concerns just give the Legal team a call and please verify against job spec.
MS NID 13 is:
NOTIFICATION OF LICENSE AGREEMENT You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype Imaging Inc., its affiliates or its licensees. You acknowledge that the font software is protected by the copyright and other intellectual property law of the United States and its various States, by the copyright and design laws of other nations, and by international treaties. Your use of this font software is limited to the rights license rights granted to you in the Monotype Imaging End User License Agreement (EULA) agreed to by you at the time of purchase and you should retain a copy of such EULA for your future reference. You may not use, rent, lease, sublicense, give, lend, or distribute the font software, or any copy thereof, except as expressly provided by the EULA. The current Monotype Imaging End User License Agreement can be viewed at http://www.fonts.com/info/legal/eula/monotype-imaging.

Mac [1, 0, 0] is: 'No entry.'
MS [3, 1, 1033] is: 'The origins of Bookman Old Style lie in the typeface called Oldstyle Antique, designed by A C Phemister circa 1858 for the Miller and Richard foundry in Edinburgh, Scotland. Many American foundries made versions of this type which eventually became known as Bookman. Monotype Bookman Old Style roman is based on earlier Lanston Monotype and ATF models. The italic has been re drawn following the style of the Oldstyle Antique italics of Miller and Richard. Although called 'Old Style', the near vertical stress of the face puts it into the transitional category. A legible and robust text face.'

Bookman Old Style Italic (Bookosi.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BookmanOldStyle-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Bookman Old Style Italic (Bookosi.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BookmanOldStyle-Italic', Everything looks good.

MS NID 7/13

License text, if Trademark (NID 7) is 'The Monotype Corporation'

License text contains 'Monotype Imaging Inc'.

NOTIFICATION OF LICENSE AGREEMENT You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype Imaging Inc., its affiliates or its licensees. Your use of this font software is limited to the rights license rights granted to you in the Monotype Imaging End User License Agreement (EULA) agreed to by you at the time of purchase and you should retain a copy of such EULA for your future reference. You may not use, rent, lease, sublicense, give, lend, or distribute the font software, or any copy thereof, except as expressly provided by the EULA. Bookman Old Style Italic (Bookosi.ttf)

name

Mac and MS NID 10

Mac and MS name table entries should be the same (English).

Entries are different.
Mac [1, 0, 0] is: 'No entry.'
MS [3, 1, 1033] is: 'The origins of Bookman Old Style lie in the typeface called Oldstyle Antique, designed by A C Phemister circa 1858 for the Miller and Richard foundry in Edinburgh, Scotland. Many American foundries made versions of this type which eventually became known as Bookman. Monotype Bookman Old Style roman is based on earlier Lanston Monotype and ATF models. The italic has been re drawn following the style of the Oldstyle Antique italics of Miller and Richard. Although called 'Old Style', the near vertical stress of the face puts it into the transitional category. A legible and robust text face.'

Mac NID 0, Copyright.

Mac NID 0 is 'Digitized data copyright The Monotype Corporation 1991-1995. All rights reserved. Bookman Old Style™ is a trademark of The Monotype Corporation which may be registered in certain jurisdictions.'
It should follow this structure: 'Copyright (c) XXXX - XXXX /entity/. All rights reserved.'

Bookman Old Style Bold (Bookosb.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

Mac [1, 0, 0] is: 'No entry.'
MS [3, 1, 1033] is: 'The origins of Bookman Old Style lie in the typeface called Oldstyle Antique, designed by A C Phemister circa 1858 for the Miller and Richard foundry in Edinburgh, Scotland. Many American foundries made versions of this type which eventually became known as Bookman. Monotype Bookman Old Style roman is based on earlier Lanston Monotype and ATF models. The italic has been re drawn following the style of the Oldstyle Antique italics of Miller and Richard. Although called 'Old Style', the near vertical stress of the face puts it into the transitional category. A legible and robust text face.'

Bookman Old Style Bold Italic (Bookosbi.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BookmanOldStyle-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BookmanOldStyle-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

name

MS NID 7/13

License text, if Trademark (NID 7) is 'The Monotype Corporation'

License text contains 'Monotype Imaging Inc'.
Normally you should just keep it as it was in the original data (often that entry is non-existing). Just double check. It shouldn't be related to Monotype Imaging Inc! In case of concerns just give the Legal team a call and please verify against job spec.
MS NID 13 is:
NOTIFICATION OF LICENSE AGREEMENT You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype Imaging Inc., its affiliates or its licensees. You acknowledge that the font software is protected by the copyright and other intellectual property law of the United States and its various States, by the copyright and design laws of other nations, and by international treaties. Your use of this font software is limited to the rights license rights granted to you in the Monotype Imaging End User License Agreement (EULA) agreed to by you at the time of purchase and you should retain a copy of such EULA for your future reference. You may not use, rent, lease, sublicense, give, lend, or distribute the font software, or any copy thereof, except as expressly provided by the EULA. The current Monotype Imaging End User License Agreement can be viewed at http://www.fonts.com/info/legal/eula/monotype-imaging.

MS [3, 1, 1033] is: 'The origins of Bookman Old Style lie in the typeface called Oldstyle Antique, designed by A C Phemister circa 1858 for the Miller and Richard foundry in Edinburgh, Scotland. Many American foundries made versions of this type which eventually became known as Bookman. Monotype Bookman Old Style roman is based on earlier Lanston Monotype and ATF models. The italic has been re drawn following the style of the Oldstyle Antique italics of Miller and Richard. Although called 'Old Style', the near vertical stress of the face puts it into the transitional category. A legible and robust text face.'

Bookman Old Style Bold Italic (Bookosbi.ttf)

OS/2 and head

sTypeAsc/Desc and unitsPerEm

The result of sTypoAscender – sTypoDescender should match or exceed the unitsPerEm value.

The result of sTypoAscender – sTypoDescender (1924) should match or exceed the unitsPerEm value (2048), but it is smaller. Consciously?

Font has no PostScript names.
